com.jrfom.gw2.api.model

Class GwApiError

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Throwable
      • java.lang.Error
        • com.jrfom.gw2.api.model.GwApiError
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable

    @Gw2ApiVersion(value="v1")
public class GwApiError
extends Error
    Represents the error object returned from the Guild Wars 2 API when an invalid parameter is passed to a method. This error will be thrown whenever such a response is received from the remote service. You can either ignore it, or use a try...catch to trap it.
